<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<objectModel xsi:schemaLocation="http://standards.ieee.org/IEEE1516-2010 http://standards.ieee.org/downloads/1516/1516.2-2010/IEEE1516-DIF-2010.xsd" xmlns="http://standards.ieee.org/IEEE1516-2010" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
    <modelIdentification>
        <name>UCATT FOM (U-FOM) Extension Base Module</name>
        <type>FOM</type>
        <version>1.0</version>
        <modificationDate>2021-11-15</modificationDate>
        <securityClassification>unclassified</securityClassification>
        <purpose>Live2LiveSim interoperability</purpose>
        <applicationDomain>Training</applicationDomain>
        <description>This module provides a common base for UCATT FOM modules. It contains common datatypes definitions.</description>
        <useLimitation></useLimitation>
        <useHistory>Removed errant UFOM ENUM dependencies from the RPR-FOM</useHistory>
        <poc>
            <pocType>Release authority</pocType>
            <pocName>NMSG-140</pocName>
            <pocOrg>NATO</pocOrg>
        </poc>
        <reference>
            <type>Dependency</type>
            <identification>UCATT-FOM-Enumerations</identification>
        </reference>
        <reference>
            <type>Text Document</type>
            <identification>SISO-STD-001.1-2015 Standard for Real-time Platform Reference Federation Object Model</identification>
        </reference>
        <other></other>
        <glyph type="png" height="80" width="64" alt=""></glyph>
    </modelIdentification>
    <objects>
        <objectClass>
            <name>HLAobjectRoot</name>
        </objectClass>
    </objects>
    <interactions>
        <interactionClass>
            <name>HLAinteractionRoot</name>
        </interactionClass>
    </interactions>
    <dataTypes>
        <simpleDataTypes/>
        <arrayDataTypes>
            <arrayData>
                <name>AdvancedDamageStatePlatformLengthlessArray</name>
                <dataType>AdvDamageStructPlatform</dataType>
                <cardinality>Dynamic</cardinality>
                <encoding>HLAvariableArray</encoding>
                <semantics>Platform (vehicles, vessels, airassets) array of advanced damage state(s)</semantics>
            </arrayData>
            <arrayData>
                <name>AdvancedProtectiveMeasuresPlatform</name>
                <dataType>Enum_Platform_Protective_Measures</dataType>
                <cardinality>Dynamic</cardinality>
                <encoding>HLAvariableArray</encoding>
                <semantics>A DO of type platform may have one or more active/passive protective measures available. This datatype does not specify amount or operational status in the array format.</semantics>
            </arrayData>
            <arrayData>
                <name>AdvancedDamageStateLifeformLengthlessArray</name>
                <dataType>AdvDamageStructLifeform</dataType>
                <cardinality>Dynamic</cardinality>
                <encoding>HLAvariableArray</encoding>
                <semantics>Lifeform (humans, animals) array of advanced damage state</semantics>
            </arrayData>
            <arrayData>
                <name>AdvancedProtectiveMeasuresLifeform</name>
                <dataType>Enum_Lifeform_Protection_Measures</dataType>
                <cardinality>Dynamic</cardinality>
                <encoding>HLAvariableArray</encoding>
                <semantics>A DO of typelifeform may have one or more passive protective measures available. This datatype does not specify amount or operational status in the array format.</semantics>
            </arrayData>
            <arrayData>
                <name>AdvancedDamageStateInfrastructureLengthlessArray</name>
                <dataType>AdvDamageStructInfrastructure</dataType>
                <cardinality>Dynamic</cardinality>
                <encoding>HLAvariableArray</encoding>
                <semantics>Infrastrucure (buildings) array of advanced damage state(s)</semantics>
            </arrayData>
        </arrayDataTypes>
        <fixedRecordDataTypes>
            <fixedRecordData>
                <name>AdvDamageStructPlatform</name>
                <encoding>HLAfixedRecord</encoding>
                <semantics>This fixed record will describe the current damage state with top level 1 down to level 4 as described in the MSG-140 Report, Annex A, DOStatus table reference. The top level enumeration values are also defined in the enumerated data table 'Enum_Advanced_Platform_Damage_State_L1' for UCATT-FOM documentation reference concerning the primary functions of entities: move, engage, communicate, observe and perform logistics.</semantics>
                <field>
                    <name>L1_Category</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Platform_Damage_State_L1</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 1 concerns the primary functions of entities: move, engage, communicate, observe and perform logistics.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field notes="UCATTnoteBase1">
                    <name>L2_SecondaryFunctions</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Platform_Damage_State_L2</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 2 concerns useful secondary functions of entities.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L3_Repair</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Platform_Damage_State_L3</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 3 concerns maintenance and repair activities.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L4_C4ISR</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Platform_Damage_State_L4</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 4 concerns details regarding C4ISR systems.</semantics>
                </field>
            </fixedRecordData>
            <fixedRecordData>
                <name>AdvDamageStructLifeform</name>
                <encoding>HLAfixedRecord</encoding>
                <semantics>This fixed record will describe the current damage state with top level 1 down to level 3 as described in the MSG-140 Report, Annex A DO Status table reference. The enumeration values are also defined in the enumerated data table 'Enum_Advanced_Lifeform_Damage_StateL1-L3' for UCATT-FOM documentation reference. 
In addition, a fixed record is used for treatments levels passed, defined in the Enum_Wounding_TreatmentTier</semantics>
                <field>
                    <name>L1_Category</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Lifeform_Damage_State_L1</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 1 concerns the primary functions of an individual (move, communicate, engage).</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L2_WoundedArea</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_ALDS_Wounding_Area_L2</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 2 - Sublevel category: wounded area</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L3_WoundType</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_ALDS_Wounding_Type_L3</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 3 - Sublevel category: wound type</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>Treatment</name>
                    <dataType>AdvTreatment</dataType>
                    <semantics>A container for treatment in order to facilitate for multiple treatments through the evacuation chain. This container only specifies which treatment levels the DO has passed. The detailed type and success of treatment is not supported.</semantics>
                </field>
            </fixedRecordData>
            <fixedRecordData>
                <name>AdvTreatment</name>
                <encoding>HLAfixedRecord</encoding>
                <semantics>These are common tier levels for treatments throughout the MEDEVAC/CASEVAC chain. The record specifies the passed treatment levels.</semantics>
                <field>
                    <name>CasualtyCollectionPoint</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Casualty collection point, used for assembly, triage (sorting), medical stabilisation and subsequent evacuation of casualties.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>Role1</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Role 1, can provide triage, first aid and lifesaving measures.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>Role2</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Role 2, can provide triage and resuscitation, treatment and holding of patients until they can be returned to duty or evacuated, emergency dental treatment and emergency surgery.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>Role3</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Role 3, can provide specialist diagnostic, specialist surgical, preventive medicine, food inspection, dentistry and operational stress management services. Classically this is a field hospital.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L1_CareUnderFire</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 1 - Care under fire</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L2_BasicFirstAid</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 2 - Basic first aid</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L3_FieldMedic</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 3 - Field medic</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L4_AssemblyArea</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 4 - Assembly area</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L5_Hospital</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 5 - Hospital</semantics>
                </field>
            </fixedRecordData>
            <fixedRecordData>
                <name>AdvDamageStructInfrastructure</name>
                <encoding>HLAfixedRecord</encoding>
                <semantics>This fixed record will describe the current damage state with top level 1 down to level 2 as described in the MSG-140 Report Annex A DO Status table reference. The top level enumeration values are also defined in the enumerated data table 'Enum_Advanced_Infrastructure_Damage_State_L1' for UCATT-FOM documentation reference.</semantics>
                <field>
                    <name>L1_Category</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Infrastructure_Damage_State_L1</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 1 provides the primary function of infrastructure to the training audience (e.g. a wall provides cover and/or protection, a bridge can enable personnel and vehicles to cross a gap).</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>L2_Subcategory</name>
                    <dataType>Enum_Advanced_Infrastructure_Damage_State_L2</dataType>
                    <semantics>Level 2 provides degraded functions of infrastructure to the training audience.</semantics>
                </field>
            </fixedRecordData>
            <fixedRecordData>
                <name>MountedOnPlatform</name>
                <encoding>HLAfixedRecord</encoding>
                <semantics>This fixed record will describe tethering of a DOPlayer or a DONonHuman to a Platform object. Example: Indication if an (mechanized) infantryman is mounted on an APC or IFV.</semantics>
                <field>
                    <name>Mounted</name>
                    <dataType>HLAboolean</dataType>
                    <semantics>True if DO is mounted; false if DO is dismounted.</semantics>
                </field>
                <field>
                    <name>Platform</name>
                    <dataType>EntityIdentifierStruct</dataType>
                    <semantics>Platform where DO is mounted.</semantics>
                </field>
            </fixedRecordData>
        </fixedRecordDataTypes>
        <variantRecordDataTypes/>
    </dataTypes>
    <notes>
        <note>
            <label>UCATTnoteBase1</label>
            <semantics>Refer to MSG-098 ANNEX D – DO STATUS DEFINITION</semantics>
        </note>
    </notes>
</objectModel>
